."},{"content":"Set Varoma aside and carefully add half of the cooked potatoes from Varoma into mixing bowl. Stir with aid of spatula and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add remaining potatoes and reserved green beans into mixing bowl and stir with aid of spatula. Cook <b>5-10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b> or until lamb and potatoes are tender. Serve garnished with extra thyme."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","We recommend buying lamb that is already diced. If you choose to dice your own lamb, please adjust cooking time accordingly as the meat may become overcooked depending on the cut used."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 30m","4 portions"]}